  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis power-law model coefficients are drawn from the experimental regression reported in the literature; the primary regression source is cited via referencesIdentifier.",
  "referencesIdentifier": "https://doi.org/10.1002/jbm.a.32519",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/hemolysis-tolerance-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
